(168, 4, 'Harissa', ' 1 tsp  garlic (lasan) paste <br> \n5 cup mutton stock <br> \n1 tsp  ginger (adrak) paste <br> \n1/2 cup ghee<br> \n1/2 tsp black pepper (kali mirch) <br> \n2 cups tomato (tamatar) puree <br> \nsalt (namak) to  taste<br> \n2 medium onion (pyaj) sliced<br> \n20  g', '<li>Soak the wheat in water for seven to eight hours. </li> \n<li>In a wide pot mix in wheat, salt and 1 1/2 liter water and stir fry it on medium flame till tender.</li> \n<li>Take another pot, mix in meat, salt, whole green chilies, ginger, garlic paste, ', '2013-03-17 09:24:57', '2013-03-17 09:24:57'),
