(188, 6, 'Chinese\r\n              Chili Chicken', '500 -600 gms Boneless Chicken <br>\n         2 tbsp Soya Sauce <br>\n         1 Egg <br>\n         2 tbsp Corn Flour/Corn Starch<br>\n         5-6 Chopped Green Chilies<br>\n         2 Green Onion Chopped<br>\n         1 tsp Garlic Paste <br>\n         Salt to t', '<li>Cut the boneless chicken pieces into1 " cubes. </li>\n          <li>Take 1tbsp. Soya sauce, 1tbsp. corn flour, salt, egg in a bowl\n            and marinate chicken pieces in the the mixture for about 10-15\n            minutes. </li>\n          <li>Heat ', '2013-03-17 09:28:04', '2013-03-17 09:28:04'),
(189, 6, 'Hot Sour Soup', '2 tbsp Chili Sauce <br>\n         11/2 tbsp Corn Flour / Corn Starch <br>\n         1 tbsp Soya Sauce <br>\n         2 tbsp Vinegar <br>\n         2 tbsp Capsicum Chopped <br>\n         2 tbsp Spring Onions Chopped 2 tbsp Tomato Sauce <br>\n         2 tbsp Carr', '<li>Mix 4 cups of water, chili sauce, soya sauce, vinegar, sugar,\n            salt, pepper powder and ajinomoto and bring to boil. </li>\n          <li>Now add all the chopped vegetables except paneer . </li>\n          <li>Cook for a minute on a medium hea', '2013-03-17 09:28:12', '2013-03-17 09:28:12'),
(190, 6, 'Veg\r\n              Manchurian', '2 cups Grated Cabbage<br>\n         2 cups Grated Carrots <br>\n         1 Chopped Spring Onion<br>\n         2 Chopped Green Chilies<br>\n         3-4 Crushed Garlic Flakes <br>\n         2 tbsp Corn Starch or Flour <br>\n         Oil for deep frying <br>\n    ', '<li>Mix grated cabbage and carrots and squeeze the water out from\n            them. </li>\n          <li>Now in a bowl take the squeezed cabbage and carrots and mix 1\n            tbsp. corn starch and add few chopped chilies and little salt to it.\n        ', '2013-03-17 09:28:21', '2013-03-17 09:28:21'),
(191, 6, 'Gobhi Manchurian', '1 medium Gobhi (Cauliflower)<br>\n         3/4 cup Flour (Maida) <br>\n         1 tbsp Corn Flour <br>\n         Salt to taste <br>\n         1 Chopped green chili <br>\n         11/2 tbsp Garlic Paste<br>\n         11/2 tbsp Ginger Paste<br>\n         1 cup fin', '<li>Make a paste of maida, corn flour and salt using water. </li>\n          <li>Take a tsp. of ginger and garlic paste, add it to the paste.\n          </li>\n          <li>Dip the gobi florets in the paste and deep fry till golden brown.\n            Keep a', '2013-03-17 09:28:29', '2013-03-17 09:28:29'),
(192, 6, 'Spring Rolls', 'Cover :<br>\n         250 gms. All purpose flour (Maida) <br>\n         1 Egg <br>\n         Little Salt <br>\n         Water to make batter <br>\n         Filling :<br>\n         2- 3 Carrots Grated) <br>\n         1 cup leeks shredded and well washed (white se', '<li>Sift the flour and add salt, egg and water and make a smooth\n            batter. </li>\n          <li>Heat little oil in a flat non-stick pan and add enough batter so\n            that it covers the base of the pan. </li>\n          <li>Cook both sides o', '2013-03-17 09:28:37', '2013-03-17 09:28:37'),
(193, 6, 'Sweet Sour Fish', '15 pieces boneless Fish <br>\n         21/2 tbsp Corn Flour / Corn Starch <br>\n         11/2 tbsp Soya Sauce <br>\n         11/2 tbsp Vinegar <br>\n         3/4 cup Chicken Stock <br>\n         3tbsp Spring Onions (chopped) <br>\n         2 tbsp Tomato Sauce <', '<li>Take 1tbsp soya sauce, 1 tbsp corn flour, salt &amp; pepper in a\n            bowl and form a mixture. </li>\n          <li>Cover fish pieces with the above mixture evenly. </li>\n          <li>Heat oil in a wok / kadhai and deep fry the fish pieces till', '2013-03-17 09:28:47', '2013-03-17 09:28:47'),
(194, 6, 'Veg Chowmein', '1 Packet Noodles<br>\n         1 Onion Sliced <br>\n         1 Capsicum Sliced <br>\n         1 Cabbage Shredded <br>\n         1 Carrot Sliced <br>\n         1/2 cup Beans Chopped <br>\n         2 tbsp Soya Sauce <br>\n         1 tbsp Vinegar <br>\n         1 tb', '<li>Boil Noodles in enough water.</li>\n          <li> Take care do not overcook. </li>\n          <li>Strain Noodles through cold water 2-3 times and drain water and\n            set aside, add few drops of oil to the noodles to avoid sticking.\n          </', '2013-03-17 09:28:55', '2013-03-17 09:28:55'),
(195, 6, 'Chilli Paneer Dry', '\r\n  500 gms Paneer or Cottage Cheese (cut in cubbes) <br>\r\n2 Onions (Sliced) <br>\r\n5-6 Garlic Cloves (chopped) <br>\r\n1 Bunch Spring Onions (chopped) <br>\r\n3 tblsp Tomato Ketchup <br>\r\n1 tblsp Chilli Sauce <br>\r\n2 tblsp Soy Sauce <br>\r\n1 tsp Vinegar <br>\r\n', '<li>Heat oil in a wok or kadai.Add onion,garlic and spring onions.</li>\r\n<li>Fry till they turn soft.</li>\r\n<li>Add ketchup,chilli sauce,soy sauce &amp; vinegar.Cook for 2-3 minutes stirring continously.</li>\r\n<li>Add paneer cubes &amp; bell peppers.Stir ', '2013-03-17 09:29:03', '2013-03-17 09:29:03'),
(196, 7, 'Baingan Bake', '2 meduim sized  sliced Brinjals <br>\n1 tblsp  Oil <br>\n6 - 7 Tomato (Tamatar) <br>\n2 flakes  chopped  Garlic (Lasun) <br>\n2 - 3 chopped Onion (Pyaj) <br>\n1/2 tsp  Red Chili Powder (Lal Mirchi) <br>\n1/4 tsp  Thyme (Ajwain)<br>\n1 tsp  Sugar<br>\n1/2 cup  Cot', '<li>Slice the brinjals. </li> \n<li>Heat oil in a nonstick pan and spread the brinjals over the pan when the oil is hot. </li> \n<li>Cover and cook on low flame till they are soft. </li> \n<li>Sprinkle little salt, cover and cook till the brinjal slices are ', '2013-03-17 09:29:19', '2013-03-17 09:29:19'),
(197, 7, 'Baked \r\n\r\nVegetables', '1 cup chopped Mixed Boiled Vegetables (French beans,carrots,cauliflower,Green peas) <br>\n\n2 chopped Onions <br>\n\n4 tblsp chopped Capsicum <br>\n\n1 chopped Tomatoes <br>\n\n&Acirc;&frac12; - 1 tsp Chili Powder<br>\nA pinch Garam Masala <br>\n\n2 tblsp chopped Co', '<li>Heat the oil and fry the onions for &Acirc;&frac12; minute. </li> \n<li>Add the capsicum and tomatoes and fry again for 2 minutes. </li> \n<li>Add the vegetables, chilli powder, garam masala, coriander and salt and cook for a few minutes. </li> \n<li>Spr', '2013-03-17 09:29:28', '2013-03-17 09:29:28'),
(198, 7, 'Beans Salad', '1/4 cup White beans (Chowli )<br>\n1/4 cup  Red kidney beans (Rajma) <br>\n1/4 cup  Green grams (whole moong) <br>\n100 gms  French beans <br>\n1medium sized  Onion <br>\n1/2 cup Fresh coriander <br>\n1/3 cup Mint <br>\n2 Green chillies <br>\n3 tblsp Lemon Juice ', '<li>Wash white cow beans and kidney beans separately. </li> \n<li>Soak them separately, overnight in plenty of water. wash and soak the green moong beans for about two hours. </li> \n<li>Boil the three dry beans separately in salted water till soft. drain a', '2013-03-17 09:29:36', '2013-03-17 09:29:36'),
(199, 7, 'Besan Ka Cheela', '2 cups Besan <br>\n1 large finely chopped Onion <br>\n1 finely chopped Green Chilli <br>\n1 bunch leaves finely chopped Coriander <br>\n1 tsp Ajwain <br>\n1 tsp Black Pepper Powder <br>\n1/2 tsp Red Chilli Powder <br>\n1 tsp Chat Masala <br>\n1 tsp Coriander Powd', '<li>Put all the ingredients except water in a big bowl. </li> \n<li>Now start adding small quantities of water to make a smooth batter, so that there should be no lumps in it. </li> \n<li>Add water till it comes to a dropping consistency or just like dosa b', '2013-03-17 09:29:49', '2013-03-17 09:29:49'),
(200, 7, 'Broccoli Soup', '500 gms Broccoli <br>\n1 medium sized Onion <br>\n4 cloves Garlic <br>\n2 inches Celery Stalk<br> \n4 cups Stock or water <br>\n1 Cup Low fat milk <br>\nSalt to taste<br>\nWhite pepper powder to taste<br>', '<li>Cut broccoli into small florets and wash well. soak in salted water for ten to fifteen minutes and drain. </li> \n<li>Peel and roughly chop onion and garlic. wash and chop celery stalk. </li> \n<li>Boil or dry roast almonds on medium heat till almond sk', '2013-03-17 09:29:57', '2013-03-17 09:29:57'),
(201, 7, 'Garlic Tomato \r\n\r\nSoup', '6 medium sized Tomatoes<br>\n2 cloves Garlic <br>\n10 gm Gelatin powder <br> \n2 Bay leaves <br>\n&Acirc;&frac12; tsp crushed Pepper Corn <br>\n&Acirc;&frac12;  tsp Mixed herbs <br>\nSalt to taste<br>\n4 tblsp Port wine (optional) <br>\n2 tsp skimmed Milk Yogurt ', '<li>Wash and finely chop the tomatoes. peel garlic and crush. soak the gelatin quarter cup cold water and keep. </li> \n<li>Cook the tomatoes in a saucepan along with the crushed garlic, bay leaves and cook the tomatoes in a saucepan along with the crushed', '2013-03-17 09:30:05', '2013-03-17 09:30:05'),
(202, 7, 'Low Calorie Dal \r\n\r\nMakhani', 'Punjabi Dal Makhani finds a place in almost all Indian restaurant menus. It is a staple in every punjabi household as well. The original recipe makes it rich and high in fat content because of the ghee and cream. These days because of the rise in health c', '<li>Soak the dal and rajma overnight in water. The amount of water should be double the amount of dal and rajma as they are going to get double in volume upon soaking.</li>\r\n          <li>Drain the water. In a pressure cook add dal, rajma, moti elaichi, c', '2013-03-17 09:30:15', '2013-03-17 09:30:15'),
(203, 7, 'Macroni In \r\n\r\nHurry', '100 gms  Macroni<br>\n1 chopped  Onion (Pyaj) <br>\n1 each yellow, red, green Capsicum (Shimla Mirch) <br>\n2 tblsp  Ketuchup<brt>\n1/2 tsp Red Chilly<br>\nLittle White Pepper<br>\n1 tblsp  Butter<br>\n Cheese for garnish<br></brt>', '<li>Chop the vegetables. </li> \n<li>Heat oil and add onions and capsicums. </li> \n<li>When they tender add sauce, chilly powder, white pepper and salt. </li> \n<li>Mix well and then add macroni. </li> \n<li>When fully mixed garnish with grated cheese. </li>', '2013-03-17 09:30:24', '2013-03-17 09:30:24'),
(204, 7, 'Masala Noodles', '1 packet  Noodles<br>\n2 Onion (Pyaj) <br>\n3 - 4 chopped  Tomato (Tamatar) <br>\n4 tsp  chopped  Coriander Leaves (Dhania Patta) <br>\n1 "  chopped  Ginger (Adrak) <br>\n3 - 4 flakes chopped Garlic (Lasun) <br>\n4 5 chopped  Green chilli (Hari mirch) <br>\n1/2 ', '<li>Boil the noodles as directed on the pack. </li> \n<li>Drain them in a strainer and wash with cold water. Keep aside. </li> \n<li>Heat oil in a nonstick pan and fry garlic, ginger, green chillies and onions until they are golden. </li> \n<li>Add tomatoes ', '2013-03-17 09:30:33', '2013-03-17 09:30:33'),
(205, 7, 'Mix veg \r\n\r\nPancakes', '<b> For pancake:</b><br>\n40 gms  Fine Wheat Flour  (Maida) <br>\n100 ml Milk <br>\n1/2 Egg <br>\n3 tsp  Oil <br>\na pinch of  Salt <br><b> For Filling:</b><br>\n50 gms  Potato (Aloo) <br>\n50 gms  Cauliflower (Phool gobi) <br>\n50 gms  Carrot (Gajar) <br>\n75 gms', '<li>To make the pancakes sift the flour along with the salt. </li> \n<li>Add the egg and gradually add the milk. </li> \n<li>Mix and beat thoroughly till the batter is smooth and free of lumps. </li> \n<li>Allow the batter to remain in a cool piece for about', '2013-03-17 09:30:42', '2013-03-17 09:30:42'),
(206, 7, 'Moong Dal Panki', '50 grams Moong Dal  <br>\n1 tblsp fresh Curd <br>\n2 Green Chilies  <br>\n1 tsp Gram Flour (besan) <br>\nA pinch Asafoetida <br>\n1 tblsp chopped coriander <br>\nA pinch sugar <br>\n1/2 tsp Lemon Juice <br>\nSalt to taste <br>', '<li>Soak the moong dal in water for 2 hours. drain. </li> \n<li>Grind with the fresh curds and green chilies. </li> \n<li>Add the gram flour, asafoetida. </li> \n<li>Grease balana leaves lightly. </li> \n<li>Spread 1 tablespoon of the mixture on one leaf and ', '2013-03-17 09:30:51', '2013-03-17 09:30:51'),
(207, 7, 'Suji Idlis', '1 cup Semolina (Suji)<br>\n 1 cup fresh Curd <br>\n1 tsp Fruit Salt (Eno) <br>\n1 cup finely chopped Cabbage<br>\n 1 chopped Onion<br> \n2 tblsp chopped Coriander<br>\n A few curry leaves <br>\n2 to 3 finely chopped Green Chilies <br>\nSalt to taste <br>', '<li>Roast the suji in pan withour oil till it changes it color to light pink on low flame. </li> \n<li>Keep it aside. </li> \n<li>When it gets cool, in a bowl take the curd and add semolina evenly. </li> \n<li>Then add the fruit salt and the remaining ingred', '2013-03-17 09:30:59', '2013-03-17 09:30:59'),
(208, 7, 'Veg Salad \r\n\r\nWith Dip', '1/4 cup  Mint leaves <br>\n4 cloves  Garlic <br>\n8-10 Cherry Tomatoes<br> \n3 medium Carrots <br>\n1 medium White Radish<br> \n4 Red Radish <br>\n8-10 leaves Ice lettuce <br>\n2 medium Cucumbers <br>\n4 cups Skimmed Milk Yogurt <br>\n1/4 tsp Sesame Seeds (white) ', '<li>Wash the cherry tomatoes &amp; cut them into halves. </li> \n<li>Peel carrots, wash &amp; cut it into finger sized pieces. peel white radish, wash &amp; cut into finger sized pieces. </li> \n<li>Clean mint leaves, wash and reserve some leaves for decora', '2013-03-17 09:31:08', '2013-03-17 09:31:08'),
(209, 7, 'Pineapple \r\n\r\nCrush', '100 ml Pineapple Juice (Ananas) <br>\n1 tblsp  Sugar (Artificial Sweetner) <br>', '<li>Make sugar syrup. </li> \n<li>Strain it and mix it into the pineapple juice. </li> \n<li>Your pineapple syrup is ready. </li> \n<li>Take &Acirc;&frac14; proportion of syrup and &Acirc;&frac34; proportion of water. </li> \n<li>Garnish it with chopped pinea', '2013-03-17 09:31:16', '2013-03-17 09:31:16'),
(210, 7, 'Cabbage Apple \r\n\r\nDelight', '1 sliced Red Cabbage (if not available then normal cabbage)<br>\n2 meduim sized sliced Apple (Sabe) <br>\n1 meduim sized  chopped  Onion (Pyaj) <br>\n1/2 cup  Vinegar<br>\n4 Pepper corns (Kalimirchi) <br>\n1/2 "  Cinnamon (Tuj/Dalchini) <br>\n2 Cloves (Lavang) ', '<li>Heat oil in a teflon-coated pan. </li> \n<li>Saute onion for a little while. </li> \n<li>Add apples and cook for a few minutes. </li> \n<li>Add sweet-n-low, cloves, peppercorns, cinnamon, vinegar, salt, lemon juice and water and bring to a boil. </li> \n<', '2013-03-17 09:31:25', '2013-03-17 09:31:25'),
(211, 7, 'Spinach Souffle \r\n\r\nSurprise', '500 gms  Spinach (Palak) <br>\n25 gms  Cottage Cheese (Paneer) (made from skimmed milk) <br>\n1 tblsp  Fine Wheat Flour  (Maida) <br>\n1 small sized  Onion (Pyaj) <br>\n1 tsp  Cinnamon (Tuj/Dalchini) Powder<br>\n1 tblsp  Oil <br>\na pinch of  Nutmeg Powder(Jaip', '<li>Chop spinach and puree it. </li> \n<li>Blend maida with a little milk and make a smooth paste. </li> \n<li>Add the rest of the milk, mix well and bring to a boil. </li> \n<li>Separate egg whites from the yolks. </li> \n<li>Heat oil in a pan, saute the cho', '2013-03-17 09:31:36', '2013-03-17 09:31:36'),
(212, 7, 'Sweet Sour \r\n\r\nVegetables', '1 sliced Onion (Pyaj) <br>\n1 tsp  Turmeric (Haldi) <br>\n1 tblsp  Oil <br>\n1 tsp  Fenugreek Seeds (Methi) <br>\n1 tsp  Cumin Seed (Jeera) <br>\n1 tsp  Aniseed (Saunf) <br>\n1/2 tsp  Onion Seeds (Kalonji) <br>\n200 gms  Brinjals (Biangan)<br>\n10 gms  chopped  G', '<li>Heat oil in a pan and fry the onions till they turn transparent. </li> \n<li>Add fenugreek, cummin, aniseed and onion seeds and fry for a minute. </li> \n<li>Add turmeric and chillies. </li> \n<li>Stir in cauliflower, cabbage and sugar (artificial sweetn', '2013-03-17 09:31:47', '2013-03-17 09:31:47'),
(213, 7, 'Ginger Ale', '1 tblsp  Lime or Lemon Juice (Nimbu) <br>\n1/2 tsp  Ginger Juice (Adrak) <br>\n2 tblsp  Sugar (Artificial Sweetner) <br>\nWater to make squash<br>\nSalt to taste<br>', '<li>Mix lemon juice and ginger juice, add sugar. </li> \n<li>Stir continuously until the sugar/sweetner dissolved. </li> \n<li>Add salt to your taste.. </li> \n<li>This is ginger ale syrup. </li> \n<li>Take &Acirc;&frac14; glass of ginger ale syrup, add water', '2013-03-17 09:31:56', '2013-03-17 09:31:56'),
(214, 7, 'Toast Fantasy', '1 big sized  Bread Slice<br>\n30 gms  Potato (Aloo) <br>\n25  gms  French Beans (Flas Beans) <br>\n20 gms  Peas (Matar) <br>\n20 gms  Carrot (Gajar) <br>\n20 gms  Cabbage (Patha gobi) <br>\n1/4 tsp  Lime or Lemon Juice (Nimbu) <br>\n1/4 tsp  Mango Powder (Amchur', '<li>Boil potato, mash and keep aside. boil green peas. </li> \n<li>Cut french beans and carrot into very small cubes and boil together. </li> \n<li>Mix all the vegetables together. </li> \n<li>Add salt, pepper powder, lemon juice and mango powder. </li> \n<li', '2013-03-17 09:32:05', '2013-03-17 09:32:05'),
(215, 7, 'Fruit Fun', '100 gms  Apple (Sabe) <br>\n75 gms Guavas (Amrood) <br>\n70 gms  Grapes (Angoor) <br>\n1 Sweet lime (Mosambi) / Orange<br>\n50 gms  Cottage Cheese (Paneer) (made from skimmed milk) <br>\n1 small bunch Mint Leaves  (Pudina Leaves) <br>\n1 tblsp  Lime or Lemon Ju', '<li>Clean and wash mint leaves. </li> \n<li>Grind the mint leaves with lemon juice, salt and pepper. </li> \n<li>Cut paneer into small cubes and dress it with mint paste. </li> \n<li>Keep aside. </li> \n<li>Peel, clean and segment the orange. </li> \n<li>Clean', '2013-03-17 09:32:14', '2013-03-17 09:32:14'),
(216, 8, 'Amritsari Fish', '8 fish fillet <br>\n         200 gms gram flour <br>\n         1 tbsp garlic paste <br>\n         1 tbsp ginger paste <br>\n         1 tsp ajwain <br>\n         1 tbsp red chili powder <br>\n         1 tbsp lemon juice <br>\n         1 egg <br>\n         100 gms ', '<li>Clean, wash and cut fish into one and a half inch size cubes.\n          </li>\n          <li>Apply salt, lime juice, ginger paste, garlic paste and red chilli\n            powder. </li>\n          <li>Keep aside for 20 minutes. </li>\n          <li>Make a', '2013-03-17 09:32:31', '2013-03-17 09:32:31'),
